and the BioC 2.5 development branch can be found at

URL:  https://hedgehog.fhcrc.org/bioconductor/trunk/madman/Rpacks/

If you have been holding off on checking new code in for fear of 
breaking the build, you may now safely do so in into the BioC 2.5 trunk. 
For those needing to fix bugs in the BioC 2.4 version of your package, 
simply point your check-ins to the BioC 2.4 URL above with the 
appropriate package name added on to the end. Unless something 
unforeseen happens, tomorrow we will be sending out an announcement on 
the BioC 2.4 release to the end-users. Thanks again for all your help in 
getting your packages ready for this release!


Patrick


